alight /əˈlaɪt/

(alighting,alighted,alights) 

1. ADJ If something is alight , it is burning. 燃烧着的 [v n ADJ, v-link ADJ] 

例： Several buildings were set alight. 几栋大楼着了火。 

2. ADJ If someone's eyes are alight or if their face is alight , the expression in their eyes or on their face shows that they are feeling a strong emotion such as excitement or happiness. 洋溢着的 [文学性] [v-link ADJ] 

例： She paused and turned, her face alight with happiness. 她停住并且转过身来，满脸洋溢着幸福。 

3. V-I If a bird or insect alights somewhere, it lands there. (鸟虫) 飞落 [文学性] 

例： A thrush alighted on a branch of the pine tree. 一只画眉落在这棵松树的一根树枝上。 

4. V-I When you alight from a train, bus, or other vehicle, you get out of it after a trip. (从车上) 下来 [正式]

